title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J. Kaiser Convention Center on 1988-03-18
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 06/2016
description:
Set 1

Iko Iko, Little Red Rooster, Brown Eyed Women, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

When Push Comes To Shove, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Solid Good show typical of the era, hot UJB and very very powerful Stella. Nice full recording

Three great AUD pulls~ I listened to all three Jon Bernstein / Andrew F audience pulls of these Spring '88 Kaiser shows this week, and all three are well worth your time!  Each show has its own highlights, and this run undoubtedly served as a springboard for a strong '88 east coast run that was just two weeks away~
